- All temp/useless files go `temp/` folder.
- After update, run `scripts/publish-extension.ps1`. Trigger GitHub workflow. Auto publish both markets.

# CI Verification Rule
Always run cargo check --workspace or cargo clippy and cargo fmt --all before pushing or releasing to ensure you haven't left broken code or unformatted files behind after refactoring or stripping dependencies. This prevents CI failures.

# PowerShell Encoding Rule
Always ensure PowerShell (.ps1) script files containing Unicode/UTF-8 character literals are saved with a UTF-8 BOM (Byte Order Mark/Signature) on Windows. Otherwise, PowerShell 5.1 parses them using ANSI/Windows-1252, causing syntax errors or character corruption.
